| responsibilities of the volunteer water co-op |
| --- |
| Responsibilities of the Water Co-Op include but are not limited to: Following the “Water User Agreement” Fees paid annually to cover various operating cost like power, insurance, repairs, emergency fund.  Voted on at AGM. Maintenance of pipes, pumps and cistern. Run by volunteers. Roadway and common space are owned by the Co-Op. Snow removal, this is because we need access to the cistern. **We are not a Homeowners Association (HOA)** |
| COMMUNITY COMMITTEE RESPONSIBILITIES |
| Responsibilities of the Community Committee include but are not limited to: Garbage removal Community concerns such as: Lawn maintenance, painting, maintaining common areas, collecting pop bottles and returning them for cash, work related to the pond such as putting in and taking out the fountain, sports field mowing and enhancements. Ideas/thoughts towards improving the community. Always looking for volunteers and ideas! In NEED OF VOLUNTEERS Anyone in our community is WELCOME TO JOIN!!! |
| responisibilities of auditor |  | Vote FOR AUDITOR |
| 6(1) The auditor is to make a report to the members On the results of the audit with respect to the reserve account, and b) On the financial statement of the association and that report must be laid out before the membership at an annual meeting of the association. As communicated, the role of the auditor is not a part of the Board and as such does not attend Board Meetings, they audit the financials at the end of the year and report on their findings. The auditor will on a one-time basis annually review bank statements, invoices, and review where and why the money was spent.  Compare the values (including general ledger) the board reports with the bank statements and provide a report for the AGM. |  | Will Prince #2 continue? Willing to return as our AUDITOR |

